iati-activity.description:
"Promote the social contract between citizens and government through the act of citizens paying taxes and government on the other hand being transparent and accountable. It is the aim of the campaign that the relationship between citizens are paying fair taxes and demanding accountability and transparency is a positive one that must be promoted to enhance the citizen-state relationship.

Specific objectives for this project are:
	To educate and sensitize Ghanaians on the need to mobilize revenues for developmentand poverty reduction;
	To educate Ghanaians on Ghanas tax system and how to comply with the countrys tax laws;
	To sensitizelaw and policy makers as well as tax administrators on tax justice;
	To create awareness and sensitize Ghanaians on the need for tax justice and empower citizens to demand tax justice."
